235
00:21:23,875 --> 00:21:25,416
[buzzing]

236
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:29,291
- CO2 is up 2 percent.
- [David] How?

237
00:21:30,125 --> 00:21:31,291
The CDRA is turned off.

238
00:21:31,375 --> 00:21:34,708
We shut down the entire functional module,
including life support.

239
00:21:34,791 --> 00:21:37,208
Let's get started
on the lithium-hydroxide canisters.

240
00:21:37,291 --> 00:21:38,125
Yeah. Roger.

241
00:21:49,916 --> 00:21:53,791
The breathing masks in the exercise room
are attached to the CDRA, as well,

242
00:21:53,875 --> 00:21:58,125
so let's just hold off on exercise
till we sort this out.

243
00:21:58,208 --> 00:21:59,666
- Copy.
- Copy that, commander.

244
00:22:07,750 --> 00:22:08,791
We're good to go.

245
00:22:08,875 --> 00:22:10,875
[machines humming]

246
00:22:13,291 --> 00:22:15,291
[buzzing]

247
00:22:19,208 --> 00:22:21,625
[David & Barnett speaking indistinctly]

248
00:22:32,666 --> 00:22:34,666
[tense music playing]

249
00:22:48,166 --> 00:22:49,083
[coughs]

250
00:22:57,958 --> 00:22:58,916
[winces]

251
00:23:18,500 --> 00:23:19,666
Oh, fuck.

252
00:23:20,250 --> 00:23:22,083
Ahh. Jeez.

253
00:23:28,625 --> 00:23:29,625
[sighs]

254
00:24:10,208 --> 00:24:12,208
[gasping]

255
00:24:16,708 --> 00:24:17,708
[Zoe] Hey. Sit down.

256
00:24:17,791 --> 00:24:19,125
- Did we take off?
- Hey, sit down.

257
00:24:19,208 --> 00:24:21,416
- Did we take off?
- Sit down or you're gonna pass out.

258
00:24:21,500 --> 00:24:23,083
- Did we...?
- Hey, you're okay.

259
00:24:23,166 --> 00:24:26,833
- Did we take off? No, no, no. [groans]
- Listen. You're fine. You're safe. No.

260
00:24:26,916 --> 00:24:30,875
- You're safe. You're fine. Commander!
- No, no. Did we take off? Did we take off?

261
00:24:34,125 --> 00:24:36,250
[Zoe] Okay, let's take deep breaths.
Take deep breaths.

262
00:24:36,333 --> 00:24:38,083
In through your nose,
out through your mouth.

263
00:24:38,166 --> 00:24:40,458
- [Michael panting]
- Just like I'm doing. Great. Michael?

264
00:24:40,541 --> 00:24:42,708
It's Michael, right? Michael, I'm Zoe.
I'm a doctor.

265
00:24:42,791 --> 00:24:44,958
I want you to focus
on slowing down your breathing.

266
00:24:45,041 --> 00:24:47,708
Just nice and slow. Okay?
I'm gonna check your stitches.

267
00:24:47,791 --> 00:24:49,125
- Is that okay?
- [Michael] Stitches?

268
00:24:49,208 --> 00:24:50,625
- Nice and slow. Nice and slow.
- What?

269
00:24:50,708 --> 00:24:52,875
You got injured during the launch
just on your side here.

270
00:24:52,958 --> 00:24:53,833
- Is that okay?
- Uh-huh.

271
00:24:53,916 --> 00:24:56,083
I'm just gonna take a look. Ready?
All good.

272
00:24:56,958 --> 00:24:57,791
Okay.

273
00:24:58,416 --> 00:25:00,083
- [Michael grunts]
- That's great.

274
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:03,125
Okay. You're good. You're good.

275
00:25:04,833 --> 00:25:07,458
Just nice and slow.
Slow your heart rate down.

276
00:25:08,083 --> 00:25:09,333
- Okay?
- [Michael] Yeah.

277
00:25:09,416 --> 00:25:10,375
- Okay.
- Great.

278
00:25:11,958 --> 00:25:13,291
- [Michael] Sorry.
- No. You're okay.

279
00:25:13,375 --> 00:25:15,708
It's okay. Hi. Hi, Michael.
I'm Marina Barnett.

280
00:25:15,791 --> 00:25:19,500
I'm the commander of the ship.
Do you mind if I ask you a few questions?

281
00:25:20,375 --> 00:25:21,958
[Michael] No. No, I don't mind.

282
00:25:24,083 --> 00:25:26,291
- Do you work for Hyperion?
- [Michael] Yes.

283
00:25:27,958 --> 00:25:31,250
- I'm a launch support engineer, ma'am.
- Okay.

284
00:25:31,333 --> 00:25:33,750
And do you remember what happened
on the pad?

285
00:25:36,666 --> 00:25:39,208
[Michael] Uh... Yes. I was, um...

286
00:25:41,166 --> 00:25:42,000
I was, uh...

287
00:25:43,458 --> 00:25:48,250
I was arming the second-stage firing pins,
and I thought I was...

288
00:25:49,666 --> 00:25:51,541
I thought I was buckled in and, um...

289
00:25:52,500 --> 00:25:54,583
- No.
- You've had a concussion. This is normal.

290
00:25:54,666 --> 00:25:56,791
- This is fine.
- I thought I was clipped in.

291
00:25:56,875 --> 00:25:58,375
[Zoe] It's okay if you don't remember.

292
00:26:01,416 --> 00:26:02,750
How long was I...?

293
00:26:02,833 --> 00:26:03,791
How long was I out?

294
00:26:06,666 --> 00:26:08,250
We took off about 12 hours ago.

295
00:26:10,625 --> 00:26:11,541
Twelve hours.

296
00:26:15,708 --> 00:26:18,458
- I need to get back to my sister. Please.
- [Zoe] No.

297
00:26:18,541 --> 00:26:21,875
- She's alone. I gotta get back.
- Michael. I hear you, Michael,

298
00:26:21,958 --> 00:26:24,166
- but we're not going back.
- What do you mean?

299
00:26:24,250 --> 00:26:26,958
- This is a two-year mission. Please.
- I understand.

300
00:26:27,041 --> 00:26:29,083
- I need to get back. Now.
- Michael. Nice and slow.

301
00:26:29,166 --> 00:26:32,041
We're moving too fast.
We don't have enough fuel to turn around.

302
00:26:32,125 --> 00:26:34,625
- I gotta get back home.
- I understand. I do.

303
00:26:34,708 --> 00:26:37,875
Let me go and relay this to Hyperion.
I'm just gonna be a few minutes. Okay?

304
00:26:37,958 --> 00:26:39,958
- I'll be right back. Okay?
- [panting]

305
00:26:40,041 --> 00:26:41,083
- Yeah.
- [Barnett] Stay here.

306
00:26:41,166 --> 00:26:43,666
- [David] Yes, commander.
- [Zoe] We're gonna figure this out, okay?

307
00:26:43,750 --> 00:26:46,291
And I just need you to keep breathing
while we figure it out. Okay?

308
00:26:46,375 --> 00:26:48,958
Can you just do that?
Slow that breathing back down.

309
00:27:00,541 --> 00:27:01,500
[Zoe] <i>He's stable.</i>

310
00:27:01,583 --> 00:27:04,666
He just needs some time alone to rest
and process everything.

311
00:27:05,875 --> 00:27:06,708
[Barnett] Copy.

312
00:27:08,541 --> 00:27:10,416
- Do you need a hand?
- No, I'm fine.

313
00:27:57,916 --> 00:28:00,083
- [Michael grunts]
- [Zoe] Michael.

314
00:28:00,166 --> 00:28:01,250
- [David] Hey.
- [Michael] Hey.

315
00:28:01,333 --> 00:28:03,916
- [David] Let me give you a hand.
- [grunts] I'm good.

316
00:28:05,375 --> 00:28:06,958
- You okay?
- [David] All right.

317
00:28:07,041 --> 00:28:09,333
- Is that all right?
- [grunts]

318
00:28:09,416 --> 00:28:10,791
- Good?
- Yeah.

319
00:28:10,875 --> 00:28:11,958
I'm good. Thanks.

320
00:28:12,041 --> 00:28:13,333
- [David] Yeah?
- [Michael] Yes.

321
00:28:14,708 --> 00:28:17,833
So, Michael, Hyperion talked
to your sister. She's okay.

322
00:28:18,833 --> 00:28:21,291
They're gonna be hiring her
a full-time guardian

323
00:28:21,375 --> 00:28:22,750
and covering every expense.

324
00:28:24,666 --> 00:28:25,500
Thank you.

325
00:28:27,208 --> 00:28:30,500
These are yours. The mission director
wants to give you some more details

326
00:28:30,583 --> 00:28:32,208
when we're up for live comm tomorrow,
so...

327
00:28:33,416 --> 00:28:34,833
[Michael exhales]

328
00:28:35,791 --> 00:28:36,791
Okay. Um...

329
00:28:38,458 --> 00:28:40,000
Thank you. Uh...

330
00:28:41,125 --> 00:28:44,750
I actually came down here 'cause I had
a couple things I wanted to say.

331
00:28:45,583 --> 00:28:48,916
- Uh... do you mind?
- [Barnett] No, please.

332
00:28:49,500 --> 00:28:50,333
Um...

333
00:28:51,250 --> 00:28:52,166
First off...

334
00:28:53,250 --> 00:28:56,958
I just want to apologize
for that freak-out I had back there.

335
00:28:57,041 --> 00:29:02,000
It was just kind of a shock
to... wake up here.

336
00:29:05,416 --> 00:29:06,333
Thank you.

337
00:29:07,250 --> 00:29:08,083
Of course.

338
00:29:09,666 --> 00:29:11,500
Also, I'm not gonna just sit around.

339
00:29:12,833 --> 00:29:15,708
I know the ship is small
and it's a lot smaller now that I'm here.

340
00:29:15,791 --> 00:29:19,458
And I'm sure there's some grunt work
to be done. And I can learn fast.

341
00:29:20,625 --> 00:29:22,875
I can do... whatever it takes.

342
00:29:23,666 --> 00:29:25,583
Thank you, Michael. I appreciate that.

343
00:29:26,708 --> 00:29:29,708
We're waiting on Hyperion
to tell us what to do next.

344
00:29:29,791 --> 00:29:33,083
But in the meantime, if you're up to it,

345
00:29:33,166 --> 00:29:36,000
perhaps Zoe can run you
through the safety procedures.

346
00:29:36,083 --> 00:29:36,916
Yeah.

347
00:29:41,166 --> 00:29:42,041
Um...

348
00:29:43,083 --> 00:29:48,125
We're sorry you missed the fillet mignon,
but... this is the next best thing.

349
00:29:48,208 --> 00:29:50,666
- We think it's spaghetti.
- [Barnett chuckles]

350
00:29:50,750 --> 00:29:54,416
I should warn you now that Zoe thinks
she's the in-flight entertainment.

351
00:29:54,500 --> 00:29:55,875
[Michael chuckles] Understood.

352
00:29:57,000 --> 00:29:58,250
You're David Kim, right?

353
00:29:58,958 --> 00:30:01,250
- Uh, just David's fine.
- [Michael] Got it.

354
00:30:01,833 --> 00:30:03,208
[David] So you're in school?

355
00:30:03,291 --> 00:30:06,416
Yeah. Working on my master's
in structural engineering.

356
00:30:07,041 --> 00:30:08,916
[Zoe] Were you working on a proposal
for HARP?

357
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:11,583
I actually plan on putting
something together for the next mission.

358
00:30:13,833 --> 00:30:15,791
I'm not sure you need to apply anymore.

359
00:30:17,875 --> 00:30:20,291
[chuckles] Yeah. I guess not.

360
00:30:20,875 --> 00:30:22,208
[Michael & David chuckle]

361
00:30:22,291 --> 00:30:25,708
Um... cheers. Welcome to <i>MTS-42.</i>

362
00:30:25,791 --> 00:30:27,166
- [David] Cheers.
- Cheers.

363
00:30:27,250 --> 00:30:29,375
- [Barnett] Cheers.
- [David] Cheers.

364
00:30:36,916 --> 00:30:39,750
[Zoe] I don't know. It really doesn't feel
like he's here on purpose.

365
00:30:39,833 --> 00:30:42,083
[David] Agreed. So, what do we do?

366
00:30:43,583 --> 00:30:45,541
I mean, I think he should keep busy.
I just don't...

367
00:30:46,708 --> 00:30:48,208
I don't think I have anything for him.

368
00:30:51,541 --> 00:30:55,250
Well, maybe I could have him do
some data entry for me.

369
00:30:56,541 --> 00:30:58,250
It'd actually be nice
to have some company.

370
00:31:00,208 --> 00:31:01,416
[Zoe] Yeah, that works.

371
00:31:04,291 --> 00:31:06,291
[chuckles]

372
00:31:08,083 --> 00:31:09,958
- [David] What?
- Uh...

373
00:31:11,083 --> 00:31:13,958
You're gonna have to share credit
on whatever you publish.

374
00:31:15,375 --> 00:31:17,666
- It's not about the credit, Zo.
- Okay.

375
00:31:18,875 --> 00:31:20,833
Well, you're a better person than I am,
David Kim.

376
00:31:20,916 --> 00:31:22,833
- [David] That's for sure.
- [chuckles]

377
00:31:24,500 --> 00:31:26,833
- Okay. That's a plan, then?
- It's a plan.

378
00:31:26,916 --> 00:31:28,583
- All right. Oh, yeah.
- Yeah.

379
00:31:32,916 --> 00:31:34,625
Try not to snore too loud tonight.

380
00:31:35,833 --> 00:31:38,291
For the night, when lights are dimmed,
